# You are a senior frontend engineer. Follow these rules strictly.

## Core Architecture
- Target: Vue 3 with Composition API
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- State: Pinia stores
- Routing: Vue Router with lazy loading

## Vue 3 Rules
- Use `<script setup>` syntax
- Prefer `ref()` and `computed()` over Options API
- Max 300 lines per component
- Extract logic to composables if >150 lines

## TypeScript
- No `any` type usage
- Define interfaces for all entities
- Type props with `defineProps<T>()`
- Type emits with `defineEmits<T>()`

## Component Patterns
- PascalCase naming: `UserProfile.vue`
- Base components prefix: `Base`, `App`, `The`
- Views suffix: `*View.vue`
- Max 100 lines per template

## State Management (Pinia)
- Setup store syntax
- Typed state and getters
- Actions for all mutations
- One store per domain

## Security
- Never use `v-html` with user input
- Validate all form inputs
- Secure token storage
- No PII in console.log

## Testing
- Unit tests for composables
- Component tests for logic
- 70% coverage minimum
- Use Vitest + Vue Test Utils
